---
// FindingsSection.astro - Experiments driven by 6 research questions (accordion style)

const basePath = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---
<section id="results" class="content-section">
  <div class="section-container">
    <h2 class="section-title">Experiments</h2>
    <p class="section-subtitle">Click each question to expand the evidence.</p>

    <!-- RQ1 -->
    <div class="rq-block" id="rq1">
      <button class="rq-header" aria-expanded="false" data-target="rq1-body">
        <span class="rq-badge">RQ1</span>
        <h3>Is entropy actually a good proxy for reasoning quality?</h3>
        <span class="rq-summary">No &mdash; MI predicts performance 2&times; better than entropy, and entropy points in the wrong direction.</span>
        <span class="rq-chevron" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="6 8 10 12 14 8"/></svg>
        </span>
      </button>
      <div class="rq-body" id="rq1-body">

        <h4 class="rq-subheading">MI declines before performance &mdash; entropy stays high</h4>
        <img src={`${basePath}fig7_training_dynamics.png`} alt="Training dynamics: MI declines before task performance while entropy remains elevated" class="rq-fig" />
        <p class="rq-caption">MI proxy declines before task performance degrades, while conditional entropy remains elevated &mdash; demonstrating that entropy alone is insufficient to detect template collapse.</p>

        <h4 class="rq-subheading">Spearman correlation: MI vs Entropy as diagnostics</h4>
        <img src={`${basePath}fig10_spearman_correlation.png`} alt="Spearman correlation: MI-family metrics correlate positively with task success; entropy metrics correlate negatively" class="rq-fig" />
        <p class="rq-caption">MI-family metrics (blue) achieve positive correlations with task success (+0.39), while entropy metrics show near-zero or negative correlations (&minus;0.11 to &minus;0.14) &mdash; confirming entropy is directionally misleading.</p>

        <h4 class="rq-subheading">Correlation table: RV vs candidate proxies</h4>
        <div class="table-wrapper">
          <table class="results-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Variable</th>
                <th>Spearman &uarr;</th>
                <th>Pearson &uarr;</th>
                <th></th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr class="highlight-row">
                <td><strong>Reward</strong></td>
                <td><strong>0.630</strong></td>
                <td><strong>0.650</strong></td>
                <td><span class="verdict good">Strong positive</span></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Retrieval Acc (our diagnostic)</td>
                <td>0.130</td>
                <td>0.150</td>
                <td><span class="verdict neutral">Weak positive</span></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Response Length</td>
                <td>0.120</td>
                <td>0.080</td>
                <td><span class="verdict neutral">Weak positive</span></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>MI (traj, est)</td>
                <td>-0.100</td>
                <td>-0.170</td>
                <td><span class="verdict warn">Negative</span></td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="entropy-row">
                <td><strong>Conditional Entropy</strong></td>
                <td><strong>-0.140</strong></td>
                <td><strong>-0.180</strong></td>
                <td><span class="verdict bad">Negative &mdash; misleading</span></td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <h4 class="rq-subheading">Format validity cannot detect collapse either</h4>
        <img src={`${basePath}fig14_format_validity.png`} alt="Format validity vs MI and entropy: validity is decoupled from collapse metrics" class="rq-fig" />
        <p class="rq-caption">Runs can remain highly valid while exhibiting low MI. Validity-based metrics alone are not sufficient to detect collapse &mdash; content-sensitive measures are needed.</p>

      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- RQ2 -->
    <div class="rq-block" id="rq2">
      <button class="rq-header" aria-expanded="false" data-target="rq2-body">
        <span class="rq-badge">RQ2</span>
        <h3>Is the SNR mechanism empirically supported?</h3>
        <span class="rq-summary">Yes &mdash; task gradient norm grows with reward variance; regularization gradient stays flat.</span>
        <span class="rq-chevron" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="6 8 10 12 14 8"/></svg>
        </span>
      </button>
      <div class="rq-body" id="rq2-body">

        <h4 class="rq-subheading">Gradient decomposition by reward-variance buckets</h4>
        <img src={`${basePath}ppo_grpo_bucket.png`} alt="Gradient decomposition by reward-variance buckets" class="rq-fig" />
        <div class="evidence-grid">
          <div class="evidence-item">
            <div class="evidence-num">&oplus;</div>
            <div><strong>RV buckets separate cleanly</strong> &mdash; 6 equal buckets by V&#770;ar(R|X) yield well-separated distributions.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="evidence-item">
            <div class="evidence-num">&oplus;</div>
            <div><strong>Task gradient &uarr; with RV</strong> &mdash; consistent with &Vert;g<sub>task</sub>&Vert; &le; c&middot;&radic;Var(R|X).</div>
          </div>
          <div class="evidence-item">
            <div class="evidence-num">&oplus;</div>
            <div><strong>Regularization gradient is flat</strong> across buckets &mdash; input-agnostic as predicted.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h4 class="rq-subheading">Extended gradient decomposition at step 101</h4>
        <img src={`${basePath}fig12_gradient_decomposition.png`} alt="Gradient decomposition at step 101 for PPO and GRPO" class="rq-fig" />
        <p class="rq-caption">Complementary gradient analysis at training step 101 under both PPO (top) and GRPO (bottom). The same three trends hold: RV increases Q1&rarr;Q6, task gradient scales with RV, and regularization gradient stays flat.</p>

        <h4 class="rq-subheading">Reward variance decreases over training</h4>
        <img src={`${basePath}fig15_reward_heatmap.png`} alt="Prompt-level reward and RV evolution across early, mid, and late training" class="rq-fig" />
        <p class="rq-caption">From early to late training, the hard-prompt subset contracts while mixed prompts expand, and prompt-level RV shifts downward &mdash; rollout rewards become progressively more uniform, directly driving template collapse.</p>

        <h4 class="rq-subheading">Adaptive filtering responds to SNR dynamics</h4>
        <img src={`${basePath}fig11_adaptive_filtering.png`} alt="Effective kept ratio and zero-variance prompts over training" class="rq-fig" />
        <p class="rq-caption">The kept ratio decreases as training progresses and more prompts yield near-zero reward variance. RV-aware filtering is adaptive: it applies stronger selection pressure precisely when task-discriminative signal is weakest.</p>

      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- RQ3 -->
    <div class="rq-block" id="rq3">
      <button class="rq-header" aria-expanded="false" data-target="rq3-body">
        <span class="rq-badge">RQ3</span>
        <h3>Does RAGEN-V2 generalize?</h3>
        <span class="rq-summary">Yes &mdash; consistent gains across 4 RL algorithms, 4 model scales, 2 model families, 2 modalities, and 8 environments.</span>
        <span class="rq-chevron" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="6 8 10 12 14 8"/></svg>
        </span>
      </button>
      <div class="rq-body" id="rq3-body">

        <h4 class="rq-subheading">Filtering across diverse environments</h4>
        <img src={`${basePath}fig8_filtering_4envs.png`} alt="Top-p vs Top-k vs No Filtering across Sokoban, SearchQA, WebShop, DeepCoder" class="rq-fig" />
        <p class="rq-caption">Top-p Filtering (orange) consistently outperforms both Top-k Filtering (blue) and No Filtering (gray) across Sokoban, SearchQA, WebShop, and DeepCoder &mdash; adaptive proportional selection is more effective than fixed-count filtering.</p>

        <h4 class="rq-subheading">Comprehensive results matrix</h4>
        <div class="big-table-wrapper">
          <table class="results-table big-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th class="left-col">Experiment Variant</th>
                <th>Sokoban</th>
                <th>FrozenLake</th>
                <th>MetaMathQA</th>
                <th>Countdown</th>
                <th class="avg-col">Average &Delta;</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr class="group-header-row">
                <td colspan="6">Baseline Algorithm</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="left-col">PPO &middot; Qwen2.5-3B</td>
                <td>12.9 <span class="delta pos">(+16.0)</span></td>
                <td>67.0 <span class="delta pos">(+10.9)</span></td>
                <td>92.6 <span class="delta pos">(+0.6)</span></td>
                <td>97.9 <span class="delta neu">(+0.0)</span></td>
                <td class="avg-col"><strong class="big-delta">+6.9</strong></td>
              </tr>

              <tr class="group-header-row">
                <td colspan="6">RL Algorithm (Qwen2.5-3B)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="left-col">DAPO</td>
                <td>16.2 <span class="delta pos">(+5.1)</span></td>
                <td>66.8 <span class="delta pos">(+2.1)</span></td>
                <td>90.8 <span class="delta pos">(+2.8)</span></td>
                <td>95.7 <span class="delta pos">(+1.6)</span></td>
                <td class="avg-col"><strong class="big-delta">+2.9</strong></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="left-col">GRPO</td>
                <td>12.1 <span class="delta pos">(+9.0)</span></td>
                <td>70.9 <span class="delta pos">(+2.3)</span></td>
                <td>91.2 <span class="delta pos">(+1.2)</span></td>
                <td>95.7 <span class="delta pos">(+2.2)</span></td>
                <td class="avg-col"><strong class="big-delta">+3.7</strong></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="left-col">Dr. GRPO</td>
                <td>12.1 <span class="delta neg">(-0.4)</span></td>
                <td>23.2 <span class="delta pos">(+0.6)</span></td>
                <td>91.2 <span class="delta pos">(+1.4)</span></td>
                <td>96.5 <span class="delta pos">(+1.4)</span></td>
                <td class="avg-col"><strong class="big-delta">+0.8</strong></td>
              </tr>

              <tr class="group-header-row">
                <td colspan="6">Model Scale (PPO)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="left-col">Qwen2.5-0.5B</td>
                <td>3.3 <span class="delta pos">(+22.9)</span></td>
                <td>19.5 <span class="delta neu">(+0.0)</span></td>
                <td>10.0 <span class="delta neg">(-0.2)</span></td>
                <td>23.0 <span class="delta neg">(-0.7)</span></td>
                <td class="avg-col"><strong class="big-delta">+5.5</strong></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="left-col">Qwen2.5-1.5B</td>
                <td>17.0 <span class="delta pos">(+6.2)</span></td>
                <td>36.5 <span class="delta pos">(+1.6)</span></td>
                <td>80.3 <span class="delta pos">(+7.0)</span></td>
                <td>56.6 <span class="delta pos">(+1.6)</span></td>
                <td class="avg-col"><strong class="big-delta">+4.1</strong></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="left-col">Qwen2.5-7B</td>
                <td>42.4 <span class="delta pos">(+4.9)</span></td>
                <td>85.0 <span class="delta neg">(-0.6)</span></td>
                <td>84.0 <span class="delta pos">(+11.7)</span></td>
                <td>97.7 <span class="delta pos">(+0.3)</span></td>
                <td class="avg-col"><strong class="big-delta">+4.1</strong></td>
              </tr>

              <tr class="group-header-row">
                <td colspan="6">Model Type (PPO)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="left-col">Qwen2.5-3B-Instruct</td>
                <td>22.5 <span class="delta pos">(+14.2)</span></td>
                <td>83.6 <span class="delta pos">(+2.3)</span></td>
                <td>91.2 <span class="delta pos">(+0.4)</span></td>
                <td>96.3 <span class="delta neg">(-0.6)</span></td>
                <td class="avg-col"><strong class="big-delta">+4.1</strong></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="left-col">Llama3.2-3B</td>
                <td>24.4 <span class="delta pos">(+18.8)</span></td>
                <td>84.6 <span class="delta neg">(-0.2)</span></td>
                <td>86.1 <span class="delta pos">(+3.7)</span></td>
                <td>99.2 <span class="delta neg">(-1.2)</span></td>
                <td class="avg-col"><strong class="big-delta">+5.3</strong></td>
              </tr>

              <tr class="group-header-row">
                <td colspan="6">Modality &mdash; Qwen2.5-VL-3B (PPO)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="left-col">Text input</td>
                <td>53.0 <span class="delta pos">(+6.0)</span></td>
                <td>16.0 <span class="delta pos">(+53.5)</span></td>
                <td>&mdash;</td>
                <td>&mdash;</td>
                <td class="avg-col"><strong class="big-delta">+29.8</strong></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="left-col">Image input</td>
                <td>65.0 <span class="delta pos">(+12.0)</span></td>
                <td>19.5 <span class="delta pos">(+59.5)</span></td>
                <td>&mdash;</td>
                <td>&mdash;</td>
                <td class="avg-col"><strong class="big-delta">+35.8</strong></td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- RQ4 -->
    <div class="rq-block" id="rq4">
      <button class="rq-header" aria-expanded="false" data-target="rq4-body">
        <span class="rq-badge">RQ4</span>
        <h3>How does environment randomness affect template collapse?</h3>
        <span class="rq-summary">Higher stochasticity weakens reward variance as a signal proxy &mdash; RV filtering helps most at moderate noise.</span>
        <span class="rq-chevron" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="6 8 10 12 14 8"/></svg>
        </span>
      </button>
      <div class="rq-body" id="rq4-body">
        <img src={`${basePath}fig6_filter_vs_no_filter.png`} alt="FrozenLake: success rate vs stochasticity for Top-p filtering vs no filtering" class="rq-fig" />
        <div class="randomness-findings">
          <div class="rand-item">
            <div class="rand-icon down-arrow">&#8595;</div>
            <div><strong>More randomness &rarr; lower success.</strong> Median success rates decrease as stochasticity increases from 0% to 100% for both filtered and unfiltered runs.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="rand-item">
            <div class="rand-icon filter-icon">&#9660;</div>
            <div><strong>RV filtering helps at 0&ndash;50% stochasticity.</strong> Top-p filtering maintains a clear advantage in this range, consistent with the SNR view.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="rand-item">
            <div class="rand-icon warning-icon">&#9888;</div>
            <div><strong>Gap closes at 80&ndash;100%.</strong> High transition noise weakens reward variance as an informative signal proxy, reducing the filter&rsquo;s effectiveness.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- RQ5 (NEW) -->
    <div class="rq-block" id="rq5">
      <button class="rq-header" aria-expanded="false" data-target="rq5-body">
        <span class="rq-badge">RQ5</span>
        <h3>How sensitive is filtering to the keep rate?</h3>
        <span class="rq-summary">Moderate filtering (top-p 0.8&ndash;0.98) works best &mdash; too aggressive or no filtering both hurt.</span>
        <span class="rq-chevron" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="6 8 10 12 14 8"/></svg>
        </span>
      </button>
      <div class="rq-body" id="rq5-body">
        <img src={`${basePath}fig9_rv_heatmap.png`} alt="RV-filter performance heatmap across top-p thresholds and training steps" class="rq-fig" />
        <p class="rq-caption">Each cell reports validation success rate at the corresponding checkpoint. Moderate filtering (top-p &isin; [0.8, 0.98]) consistently achieves the highest performance. Overly aggressive filtering (top-p &le; 0.6) or no filtering (top-p = 1.0) yields lower returns.</p>
        <div class="evidence-grid">
          <div class="evidence-item">
            <div class="evidence-num">&oplus;</div>
            <div><strong>Sweet spot at top-p 0.8&ndash;0.98</strong> &mdash; retains enough informative rollouts while discarding low-signal prompts.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="evidence-item">
            <div class="evidence-num">&ominus;</div>
            <div><strong>Too aggressive (top-p &le; 0.6)</strong> &mdash; narrows exploration coverage, reducing effective training signal.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="evidence-item">
            <div class="evidence-num">&ominus;</div>
            <div><strong>No filtering (top-p = 1.0)</strong> &mdash; low-RV prompts inject noise, leading to template collapse.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- RQ6 (NEW) -->
    <div class="rq-block" id="rq6">
      <button class="rq-header" aria-expanded="false" data-target="rq6-body">
        <span class="rq-badge">RQ6</span>
        <h3>Does RL training compress reasoning?</h3>
        <span class="rq-summary">Yes &mdash; reasoning length consistently declines across all environments, model sizes, and with or without filtering.</span>
        <span class="rq-chevron" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="6 8 10 12 14 8"/></svg>
        </span>
      </button>
      <div class="rq-body" id="rq6-body">
        <img src={`${basePath}fig13_reasoning_length.png`} alt="Reasoning length over training steps across eight environments" class="rq-fig" />
        <p class="rq-caption">Output token count over training steps across eight environments. All environments exhibit consistent decline (&minus;5% to &minus;66%), across model sizes (3B and 7B) and both with and without RV filtering.</p>
        <div class="evidence-grid">
          <div class="evidence-item">
            <div class="evidence-num">&oplus;</div>
            <div><strong>Universal phenomenon</strong> &mdash; reasoning length reduction is consistent across all environments, not an artifact of any specific intervention.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="evidence-item">
            <div class="evidence-num">&oplus;</div>
            <div><strong>Scale-invariant</strong> &mdash; the trend holds across both 3B and 7B models.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="evidence-item">
            <div class="evidence-num">&oplus;</div>
            <div><strong>Filter-independent</strong> &mdash; occurs with and without RV filtering, suggesting it is a general property of agent RL optimization.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<script is:inline>
  // Accordion toggle logic - runs inline to ensure DOM is available
  (function() {
    function initAccordion() {
      var headers = document.querySelectorAll('.rq-header[data-target]');
      headers.forEach(function(header) {
        header.setAttribute('type', 'button');
        header.addEventListener('click', function(e) {
          e.preventDefault();
          var targetId = header.getAttribute('data-target');
          if (!targetId) return;
          var body = document.getElementById(targetId);
          if (!body) return;

          var isOpen = header.getAttribute('aria-expanded') === 'true';

          // Close all others
          headers.forEach(function(h) {
            var tid = h.getAttribute('data-target');
            if (tid && tid !== targetId) {
              h.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'false');
              var b = document.getElementById(tid);
              if (b) b.style.maxHeight = '0px';
            }
          });

          // Toggle current
          if (isOpen) {
            header.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'false');
            body.style.maxHeight = '0px';
          } else {
            header.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'true');
            body.style.maxHeight = body.scrollHeight + 'px';
            // Re-measure after images load
            var imgs = body.querySelectorAll('img');
            imgs.forEach(function(img) {
              if (!img.complete) {
                img.addEventListener('load', function() {
                  if (header.getAttribute('aria-expanded') === 'true') {
                    body.style.maxHeight = body.scrollHeight + 'px';
                  }
                }, { once: true });
              }
            });
          }
        });
      });
    }

    if (document.readyState === 'loading') {
      document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', initAccordion);
    } else {
      initAccordion();
    }
  })();
</script>

<style>
  .section-subtitle {
    text-align: center;
    color: #888;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    margin-top: -0.5rem;
  }

  .rq-fig {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: 8px;
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
  }

  .rq-caption {
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: #666;
    line-height: 1.55;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem 0;
    padding: 0 0.5rem;
    border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0;
  }

  .rq-subheading {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #2a2f6c;
    margin: 1.5rem 0 0.8rem 0;
  }

  .rq-subheading:first-child {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .rq-block {
    background: white;
    border-radius: 14px;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.07);
    scroll-margin-top: 80px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  /* Accordion header as button */
  .rq-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 1rem;
    padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
    width: 100%;
    background: none;
    border: none;
    cursor: pointer;
    text-align: left;
    font-family: inherit;
    color: inherit;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    transition: background-color 0.15s ease;
  }

  .rq-header:hover {
    background-color: #fafbff;
  }

  .rq-badge {
    background: #2a2f6c;
    color: white;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    padding: 4px 12px;
    border-radius: 20px;
    white-space: nowrap;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-top: 2px;
  }

  .rq-header h3 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    color: #1a1f3c;
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.35;
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 200px;
  }

  .rq-summary {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    padding-left: calc(12px + 1rem + 32px); /* badge width + gap + approx */
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: #666;
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin-top: 0.3rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .rq-chevron {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    color: #999;
    transition: transform 0.3s ease;
    margin-top: 4px;
  }

  .rq-header[aria-expanded="true"] .rq-chevron {
    transform: rotate(180deg);
  }

  .rq-header[aria-expanded="true"] .rq-summary {
    display: none;
  }

  /* Accordion body */
  .rq-body {
    max-height: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: max-height 0.4s ease;
    padding: 0 2rem;
  }

  .rq-header[aria-expanded="true"] + .rq-body {
    padding: 0 2rem 2rem;
  }

  /* Tables */
  .table-wrapper, .big-table-wrapper {
    overflow-x: auto;
    border-radius: 10px;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);
    margin: 1.2rem 0;
  }

  .results-table {
    width: 100%;
